### 1 · Overall Art-Direction & UX philosophy

* **Laser-focused storytelling** – each scroll viewport holds one message and one product. No split attention, no extraneous links.  The page is basically a vertical carousel of hero “billboards”. ([apple.com][1])
* **Minimal cognitive load** – typography, colour and iconography are reduced to the fewest elements necessary, a play straight from the *Human Interface Guidelines* mantra of clarity and deference. ([developer.apple.com][2])
* **Whitespace as structure** – generous top/bottom margins (\~8–12 rem on desktop) create pause between stories and let product shots command the stage. Medium articles analysing Apple routinely cite “white (or very light grey) oceans” as the brand’s secret sauce. ([medium.com][3])
* **Micro-interactions, not decoration** – motion exists (parallax fades, subtle zooms) but only to reinforce hierarchy, never as an ornament.

