### 3 · Typography

| Use-case                 | Typeface & treatment                                                              | Notes                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |
| ------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Headlines**            | **SF Pro Display** 700/900, -0.022 em letter-spacing, tight line-height (\~1.05). | SF Pro is proprietary; web usage outside Apple violates the licence. Substitute the system-UI stack: `font-family:-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;` ([developer.apple.com][4], [stackoverflow.com][5]) |
| **Body copy**            | SF Pro Text 400–500, 17 px, 1.47 line-height.                                     | Keep paragraph width ≤65 ch to mirror Apple’s comfortable measure.                                                                                                                                                                                         |
| **Captions / footnotes** | SF Pro Text 400, 12 px, 1.3 lh, #6e6e73.                                          | Grey footnotes are visually demoted yet still readable on accessibility tests.                                                                                                                                                                             |

