### 7 · How to copy the *spirit* (without infringing)

1. **Build a tokenised design-system**:

   ```css
   :root{
     --ink:#1d1d1f; --paper:#ffffff; --frost:#f5f5f7;
     --radius:12px; --ease: cubic-bezier(.4,0,.2,1);
   }
   ```
2. **Type scale** (Major Third ratio 1 → 1.25): 14 / 17 / 21 / 27 / 33 / 41 / 51 / 64 px.
3. **Section template** (HTML):

   ```html
   <section class="billboard bg-paper">
     <div class="wrap">
       <h1 class="headline">Your Product</h1>
       <p class="eyebrow">Tagline goes here</p>
       <p class="cta"><a href="#">Learn more <svg …/></a></p>
       <picture>…</picture>
     </div>
   </section>
   ```
4. **CSS starter**:

   ```css
   body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;
        color:var(--ink); background:var(--paper);}
   .wrap{max-width:980px;margin-inline:auto;padding-inline:clamp(1rem,4vw,3rem);}
   .headline{font-size:clamp(2.1rem,5vw+1rem,4rem);font-weight:900;letter-spacing:-.02em;}
   .cta a{color:#0066cc;display:inline-flex;gap:.25rem;transition:color .3s var(--ease);}
   .cta a:hover{color:#004799;}
   .billboard{padding-block:clamp(6rem,12vw,12rem);text-align:center;}
   ```
5. **Legal sanity-check**: avoid Apple trademarks (logo, SF Pro web-embedding).  Use open-source “Inter”, “IBM Plex Sans” or “Poppins” for a similarly neutral, geometric voice if you need web-served fonts.

