## Quick replication checklist

* [ ] Global nav bar with blur & dark translucence
* [ ] Vertical stack of full-width billboards, each one story
* [ ] System-UI font stack, bold headings, tight tracking
* [ ] Whitespace: ≥8 rem above/below each hero
* [ ] 50-50 grid for secondary stories on desktop, single column on mobile
* [ ] Text CTAs with arrow glyph, no button boxes
* [ ] Tokenised colour scheme, ready for Dark Mode
* [ ] Lazy-loaded, high-resolution product imagery

Run through that list and you’ll have a site that *feels* unapologetically Apple-esque without crossing the line into copy-cat territory. Good luck, and ping me if you’d like deeper code reviews or Motion guidelines!

